concept_set_id: [VSAC] COVID19 ICD10CM Value Set for Down's Syndrome
concept_set_name: [VSAC] COVID19 ICD10CM Value Set for Down's Syndrome
intention: Clinical Focus: This set of values contains terms related to Down's syndrome (Trisomy 21) and is listed as a neurologic disorder on the CDC SARS-CoV-2 hospitalization surveillance case report form.; Data Element Scope: ; Inclusion Criteria: Includes Down's syndrome (Trisomy 21).

Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for a diagnosis of  rheumatoid arthritis.; Data Element Scope: This value set may use a model element related to Diagnosis.; Inclusion Criteria: Includes concepts that represent a diagnosis of rheumatoid arthritis and Felty's syndrome, including comorbidities occurring with rheumatoid arthritis such as rheumatoid polyneuropathy, rheumatoid myopathy, rheumatoid heart disease, rheumatoid vasculitis, and rheumatoid lung disease.
